        "paragraph_index": 1,
        "text": "### Linked Literature Citations for vlm_1\n\nBoth citations attached to vlm_1 carry the same shortcut code **58Sc** and point to the same primary source:\n\n| # | Shortcut | Authors | Journal | Volume | Page | Year |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | 58Sc | Schwarzenbach G., Sandera J. | *Helv. Chim. Acta* | 36 | 1089 | **1953** |\n| 2 | 58Sc | Schwarzenbach G., Sandera J. | *Helv. Chim. Acta* | 36 | 1089 | **1953** |\n\n> **Note:** Both citation rows reference the same paper by Schwarzenbach and Sandera (1953). This is a common SRD-46 pattern where the same source is linked twice — once as the original measurement reference and once as a compilation/review reference — to indicate that the value was both measured and subsequently endorsed in a critical review.",
